<p>I am getting JSON data from Neo4j OGM (Object Graph Mapping) in nested-tree like format. <a href="http://bl.ocks.org/mbostock/4063550" rel="nofollow">http://bl.ocks.org/mbostock/4063550</a></p>  <p>But for visualizing complex graphs, I need to get the JSON data in the following graphJSON format. <a href="http://bl.ocks.org/mbostock/4062045" rel="nofollow">http://bl.ocks.org/mbostock/4062045</a></p>  <p>i.e.,with nodes and links separated.</p>  <blockquote>   <p>This is for visualizing data from Neo4j using d3.js visualization   after performing various operations using Java.</p> </blockquote>